<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                    <head>No. 117.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Osborn</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-23"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 23,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 89.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herein for your information a copy
                        of a late instruction<note n="*" xml:id="d117fn1">See Mr. Evarts’s
                            instruction to Mr. Adams, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_78">page 78</ref>.</note> sent to Mr. Adams, the newly
                        appointed minister of the United States to Bolivia, respecting a proposition
                        of Chili, touching an exchange between those countries of prisoners of
                        war.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>